<Docs title="Installation" description="How to install BMB">
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <p>BMB supports multiple installation methods across different platforms.</p>

  <h2>Quick Install (Recommended)</h2>

  <h3>Unix/Linux/macOS</h3>
  <pre><code>curl -sSf https://bmb-lang.org/install.sh | sh</code></pre>

  <h3>Windows</h3>
  <pre><code>irm https://bmb-lang.org/install.ps1 | iex</code></pre>

  <h2>Build from Source</h2>

  <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Rust 1.70+ (install via <a href="https://rustup.rs">rustup</a>)</li>
    <li>Git</li>
    <li>LLVM 15+ (for native code generation)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Clone and Build</h3>
  <pre><code># Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/lang-bmb/lang-bmb
cd lang-bmb

# Build release
cargo build --release

# Install to PATH
cargo install --path bmb</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify Installation</h2>
  <pre><code># Check version
bmb --version

# Run a test program
echo 'fn main() -> i64 = 42;' > test.bmb
bmb run test.bmb</code></pre>

  <h2>Editor Support</h2>

  <h3>VS Code</h3>
  <p>Install the BMB extension from the marketplace:</p>
  <pre><code>ext install lang-bmb.vscode-bmb</code></pre>

  <h3>Other Editors</h3>
  <p>
    BMB provides a Language Server Protocol (LSP) implementation that works with any LSP-compatible editor.
    Configure your editor to use <code>bmb lsp</code> as the language server.
  </p>

  <h2>Package Manager (곳간)</h2>
  <p>
    BMB includes <strong>gotgan</strong> (곳간), a built-in package manager:
  </p>

  <pre><code># Create a new project
gotgan new my-project
cd my-project

# Add a dependency
gotgan add bmb-json

# Build and run
gotgan run</code></pre>

